Rating: 4.4  I have lived in Downtown St. Louis for over two years, and I have walked or run by Chili Mac's Diner hundreds of times. Since I work during the week, I have not gotten a chance to give it a try. This morning on a walk before work, I decided to make an impromptu stop since I saw the menu on the window features Hot Cakes. As y'all know, I am all about pancakes. The waitress was very friendly, and I was seated promptly. I immediately ordered the full stack (3) of Hot Cakes. The Hot Cakes came out quickly, which was fantastic. Why? Because these Hot Cakes were excellent. They were light and fluffy and had great flavor. For only $4.50, the portion size was quite generous, and this meal was a total bargain. The syrup was also good, and it complemented the Hot Cakes well. The diner vibe of Chili Mac's was obvious, and I hope to come back in the future to give these another try. I am really glad that I checked it out! My advice: Check it out!

Walking through Downtown St. Louis is a post-apocalyptic experience these days. It's totally abandoned. The food is dead-on diner experience - from taste, to ambiance, to clientele, to staff to menu pricing. If you have the misfortune of finding yourself in downtown St. Louis, brighten your experience by stopping here and reminding yourself of a time when Midwest America was great place to be.

From the moment you walk into this time-tested establishment, it feels as if you are in the first scene of a Cohen Brothers movie. There are three wonderful waitresses, coffee pot in hand, always on the ball, and calling you “Hun.” I order—for a total of $8–eggs over easy, bacon, toast, hash browns, and a half order of biscuits and gravy. This is THE greasy spoon that all St. Louisans need to experience. The menu is frank, straightforward, and honest. The bottom line could not be clearer: you walk in, order your favorite first meal of the day, you pay a small amount (and please tip generously), and you’re on your way. As you walk away, looking at the tacky 80s architecture of 1 Metro Square in the background, you will realize this establishment has captured an iconic piece of Americana that you can never let go. Visit Chili Macs as often as you can—like a fine wine, it never goes bad, and only gets better with age.

This place feels like a 1950's old fashioned dinner, which feels homey and comfortable while set right in the middle of Downtown St. Louis.  It's new york style seating meaning you will sit at a table with random strangers, the place is incredibly small.  A bar, 10 tables with 2 grills and a frier running.  What really makes this place great is the extremely nice waitresses, they greet you when you walk in the door, and through out the whole time they are constantly checking in on you as if you are their own son or daughter, normally I would see this as annoying but not here, not in this type of atmosphere. They will come put a hand on your shoulder and it feels very comforting during lunch on a stressful workday downtown.  It's honestly like Mom serving you lunch.  They even remember most people's lunch orders when they walk in which makes you feel valued. The prices are cheaper than big establishments in the area. The owner who runs the cash register makes it a point to ask how your day is going and the little things like that or a simple rub on the back from the waitresses is what makes this place my new favorite in st. louis.  I'm a regular now and go every week.  5 star rating.

Great diner with really cheap prices.  Enjoyed the food and it was also really quick.
Excellent greasy spoon diner. Service is very good.

Don't find these diners too often! Love the old school, hole in the wall feeling. The food is amazing and the service is excellent. The food came so quick! The resturant was packed and we got our breakfast faster then we would have at Mcdonald's! Highly recommend!
Love it. The ladies are awesome and the food is great.
Great old fashion diner with great food, great prices and great service. Highly recommend!

This is a rare treat to find these days. A classic diner with truly delicious food! Also a place with plenty of history and that has been around St. Louis since the early 1900s. Truly a good place for those that hanker for home cooking.
Good food and good prices.
Pretty decent food for VERY cheap... Don't expect a fancy gourmet meal and you will be happy!
An old school greasy spoon with an old school atmosphere

If you have never had nor ever heard of a Slinger, then this is the place to try it. Chili Mac's has, hands down, the best. The Slinger is something you should definitely experience. The service is great. The waitresses have their own language to translate your order to the cooks, which is quite entertaining. I would describe the decor as a little hole-in-the-wall/old-fashioned diner. If you aren't looking for the place when you walk by, you might walk right past it without even noticing.
Very affordable and super friendly staff.
Real diner experience, just like I remembered from my Jersey days!
Food made in front of you,  and was delicious!

It was a good atmosphere.  The staff was good.  And the Chili Mac looked good. Food cooked fresh, right in front of you. Populated by locals, that keep coming back. Don't forget to try their breakfast food as well.
BEST French toast I have ever had! As far as diners go, this was delicious.
Like everyone else said really is a true diner. Food wasn't awesome but wasn't bad. And two of us are for under 10 dollars so you can't beat that.

The whole visit started poorly when the waitress asked me if I wanted cream with my coffee and then brought me milk instead of half and half. Then when I stirred in the milk and stuck the spoon in my mouth I found crusted gravy on the bottom. Yuck! I was disappointed further when the toast came with Country Crock instead of butter and the potatoes were sitting in a puddle of grease. The staff was friendly, but even for a diner (and I like diners) this place was kind of low rent. On the plus side the food was inexpensive.
A REAL diner. The orders are directly spoken to the cook not written down! As local as it can get. The food was delicious!
👍🏼👍🏼👍🏼👍🏼👍🏼👍🏼👍🏼👍🏼👍🏼👍🏼👍🏼🍴 Sweet little place, the food was excellent !!! Awesome place for breakfast!!!🍽
Great place to eat!
Employees were super. Two women ran the place, which was busy the entire time. The food was delicious and fairly priced.
Great old fashioned dinner,  great chilli, lovely ladies who work there!
Friendly staff, extremely fast service, delicious food.
Chili's awesome
Awesome experience!!  So awesome we ate there twice for breakfast.  Definitely think you should make this a stop if your visiting.
Breakfast was great! The bacon was amazing and the service was fantastic. Would recommend, especially if you are near Busch Stadium or the Arch.
If you're looking for a "true" diner downtown, come here. Warning. Don't get the chili..! Family owned, quite a unique environment.

Best biscuits and gravy and french toast I've ever had. Usually these little diners have bland plain food, but this one is amazing. The french toast was crispy on the outside, gooey on the inside, and honestly didn't need any butter or syrup, but try it with both anyway. ;) The biscuits came out soft and piping hot. The only let down was the coffee, but the quick super friendly service made up for that and then some.
The Slingers are the BEST.
For all of you that remember what dinners are this is it.  Good food friendly service just like it should be.....
Very Friendly Staff! The French Toast was amazing! No syrup needed to enjoy this dish:)

Chili Mac's is a wonderfully authentic diner. The service is charming, prices are right and the food is consistently great. On my visit to St. Louis, I found myself there for lunch and back for breakfast.
Great breakfast and friendly staff that makes you feel like you're with family. Make sure you sit where you're told.
Amazing breakfast. Wish they were open on weekends.
Awesome place!!
Great food, great service. Love diners and this one is at the top of my list!
Chili and eggs, what can be better.  Great staff.  Well done. Henry thought short stack was wonderful.
One of the best diner experiences I've ever had. Both the food and the staff
Had breakfast here 2 days in a row. Friendly service.

We have been waiting to go here since we moved to St. Louis. Finally had an early day off from work so we decided to go here for lunch on Christmas Eve Day. The waitress (no id name tag) who had a big do was quite the surly smart ass. When my wife told her she had an attitude she snapped back I do not and and said do you want to sit here and argue about it. She single handedly ruined this experience. The owner made an attempt at apology but reading between the lines she either did not care or supported this crappy attitude. She proceeded to "comp" the meal even though I insisted on paying as there as nothing wrong with the order itself. It is possible this surly woman is the "owners" sister, there were some resemblances. The cook was pleasant, just could not believe this customer be damned attitude.
Classic diner. Great to visit
Great lunch or Breakfast spot!
Great food. Great prices. Kris (the owner) is involved and passionate about her business. Dont miss a chance to eat here!
Best biscuits and gravy, bacon and coffee I've ever had! Cooked to perfection. Fast and inexpensive. And the dated decor was cute too. Absolutely delicious!
A great breakfast and lunch spot. Classic diner, great staff, I make it a point to eat here when I'm in town.
Chili Mac's is a wonderful place - great food and great staff.  I LOVE IT and tell all my friends about it.  It's GREAT!!
Had breakfast there this am.  They knew their regulars by name and order. The ladies were real nice.
Great service,  very kind people the food is served quickly after you order (about five minutes or less) the food is phenomenal, and you fel like you are right at home!
The food is served by the group of the nicest ladies you ever meet.

MUST VISIT!  Great place for breakfast or lunch.  I have worked downtown for almost 10 years and can only say great things about this diner.  The servers take excellent care of you and the food is always good.  Even after all this time, when they see me they don't even give me a menu - they know EXACTLY what I'm going to order!  Thank you Chili Mac's Diner!
Great food. Cheap. Great people. Quick. Perfect!
